Residents of Chemolingot and Ng’inyang’ villages in Tiaty constituency in Baringo county are up in arms over the delayed completion of Nyangang river bridge that has so far claimed the lives of fifty people. The killer bridge which links Baringo and Turkana counties has been destroyed by floods more than seven times, has remained uncompleted after it collapsed during the last stages of construction
with residents now raising fears ahead of the commencement of at the long rains season . 